HEADWORD: Suspicable
<hw>Sus"pi*ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suspacabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>suspicari</ets> to suspect, akin to
<ets>suspicere</ets>. See <er>Suspect</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Liable to suspicion; suspicious.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a very <qex>suspicable</qex> business.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H.
